        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(provider-transport-fetch): bound SSE buffer to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`src/agents/provider-transport-fetch.ts` has two unbounded memory accumulation paths in `sanitizeOpenAISdkSseResponse`:\n\n1. **SSE sanitizer** (`enqueueSanitized`, line 174): Accumulates decoded chunks into a `buffer` string that only drains when a `\\n\\n` SSE event boundary is found. If data arrives without boundaries, the buffer grows unboundedly — the same OOM vector fixed for the OpenAI `parseSSE` in #96972.\n\n2. **JSON-to-SSE synthesis** (line 134): Accumulates an entire streaming JSON body into `buffer` inside a `for(;;)` read loop. A hostile or misconfigured endpoint streaming JSON without Content-Length can cause the buffer to grow without bound, exhausting process memory.\n\nThese affect every non-OpenAI provider call routed through the guarded model fetch path (OpenRouter, custom OpenAI-compatible endpoints, and proxies).\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/agents/provider-transport-fetch.ts` (+23 LoC): Added two constants:\n  - `SSE_SANITIZE_BUFFER_MAX_BYTES = 64 KiB` — caps the internal SSE sanitizer buffer between event boundaries, matching the `parseSSE` fix in #96972.\n  - `SSE_SYNTHESIZE_JSON_MAX_BYTES = 16 MiB` — caps total bytes accumulated when synthesizing a streaming JSON body into SSE frames, matching the existing `readResponseTextLimited` default.\n\n  After each chunk decode in the sanitizer (`enqueueSanitized`), a `buffer.length` check throws if the buffer exceeds 64 KiB without finding an event boundary. After each chunk in the JSON synthesis loop, a `totalBytes` check throws if the accumulated body exceeds 16 MiB.\n\n- `src/agents/provider-transport-fetch.test.ts` (+96 LoC): Added inline tests:\n  - `\"errors on oversized SSE body without event boundary in sanitizer\"` — 65 KiB SSE without `\\n\\n` → buffer cap error.\n  - `\"errors on oversized streaming JSON body without content-length in SSE synthesis\"` — 17 MiB streaming JSON → synthesis cap error.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Two unbounded memory accumulation vectors in the provider transport SSE sanitization and JSON-to-SSE synthesis paths, both of which could OOM the gateway when a hostile or misconfigured endpoint streams data without expected delimiters or Content-Length.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux x86_64, Node 22.19, OpenClaw main@9a735bea03\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  ```bash\n  node --import tsx _proof_transport_fetch.mts\n  ```\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n  ```\n  PASS  sanitizer: oversized SSE body throws buffer cap error (server sent 65.0 KiB, cap=64.0 KiB)\n  PASS  sanitizer: valid SSE with \\n\\n boundaries passes through (server sent 19 B)\n  PASS  synthesis: oversized streaming JSON body throws cap error (server sent 17.0 MiB, cap=16.0 MiB)\n  PASS  synthesis: small valid JSON body accumulates normally (server sent 11 B)\n  PASS  negative control: unbounded read would accumulate full 17.0 MiB (OOM vector confirmed)\n\n  Results: 5/5 passed\n  ```\n  75/75 unit tests passed: `pnpm test src/agents/provider-transport-fetch.test.ts --run`\n- **Observed result after fix**:\n  - Real `node:http` server delivering 65 KiB SSE without `\\n\\n` → sanitizer throws buffer cap error at 64 KiB.\n  - Real server delivering valid SSE with `\\n\\n` → passes through correctly.\n  - Real server streaming 17 MiB of JSON without Content-Length → synthesis throws cap error at 16 MiB.\n  - Real server delivering small valid JSON → accumulates and passes through normally.\n  - Negative control: without the cap, the same 17 MiB JSON body is fully accumulated in memory (confirmed OOM vector).\n- **What was not tested**: OpenAI native provider path (official `api.openai.com` uses WebSocket, not SSE sanitization); extension-level providers; the `classifyOpenAISdkStreamBody` sniff path (bounded at 2 KiB by `OPENAI_SDK_STREAM_CONTENT_SNIFF_BYTES`).\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- The `classifyOpenAISdkStreamBody` sniff function is already bounded by `OPENAI_SDK_STREAM_CONTENT_SNIFF_BYTES` (2 KiB) and is not affected.\n- The non-streaming `readResponseTextLimited` / `readProviderJsonResponse` paths were bounded in earlier Alix-007 PRs (e.g., #96768, #96762).\n\n## Risk\n\n**Low.** Both caps (64 KiB and 16 MiB) are well above any reasonable event payload or response body. If triggered, the stream errors with a clear message rather than silently terminating. The change is additive — no existing behavior is modified, only guards added. Both constants are file-local.\n\nAI-assisted; reviewed before submission.\n",
        "branch": "fix/bound-anthropic-sse-parse-buffer",
